On hold:     Oerjan

======================================================================

History:
  Called by Harlequin, Mon, 17 Mar 1997 21:08:31 -0500 (EST)
  Assigned to Andre, Mon, 24 Mar 1997 09:29:25 +0000
  Judged TRUE, Mon, 24 Mar 1997 17:43:57 +0100 (MET)
  Published, Wed, 26 Mar 1997 09:34:23 +0000

======================================================================

Judgement: TRUE

Reasons and arguments:

The only Rule that forbids negative amounts of Currencies is Rule
1596.  However that Rule only forbids Transfers that are not required
by the Rules to cause a Treasury to contain a negative quantity of
Currencies.  However, that only applies to transfers required by
another Entity than the Rules themselves. However, there are Rules
that require Currencies to be transfered from the Bank, and no Rule
would stop those from happening, even if that would cause the Bank to
hold a negative amount of the Treasury.

======================================================================

(Caller's) Arguments:

Evidently negative amounts of a currency are permissible if caused by
a rule and not by a player transfer. No rule prohibits the Bank from
having negative amounts of a currency.

======================================================================